<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a016813-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s5705"><num value="5705">§ 5705.</num><heading> Exemption</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Chapter 10 of title 5 shall not apply to the Panel, the Yukon River Joint Technical Committee, or the Advisory Committee created under <ref href="/us/usc/t16/s5704">section 5704 of this title</ref>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7a016814-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/104/43/tVII/s706">Pub. L. 104–43, title VII, § 706</ref>, <date date="1995-11-03">Nov. 3, 1995</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/109/394">109 Stat. 394</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/117/286/s4/a/126">Pub. L. 117–286, § 4(a)(126)</ref>, <date date="2022-12-27">Dec. 27, 2022</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/136/4319">136 Stat. 4319</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id7a016815-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id7a016816-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id7a016817-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2022—<ref href="/us/pl/117/286">Pub. L. 117–286</ref> substituted “Chapter 10 of title 5” for “The Federal Advisory Committee Act (5 U.S.C. App.)”.</p>
</note>
